This file contains statistics and figures from the paper, Molecular, Cellular, and Developmental Organization of the Mouse Vomeronasal organ at Single Cell Resolution by Max Hills Jr., Limei Ma, Ai Fang, Thelma Chiremba, Seth Malloy, Allison Scott, Anoja Perera, and C. Ron Yu.

The paper can be found here:

Molecular, Cellular, and Developmental Organization of the Mouse Vomeronasal organ at Single Cell Resolution

Molecular cascades separating the neuronal lineages

PCA plot of V1R and V2R pseudotime principal curves across cell types

Cell density plots across pseudotime for P14 and P56 mice

Summary of Kolmogorov-Smirnov Test


    Two-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test

data:  p14.v1r.pseudotime$v1r.pseudotime and p56.v1r.pseudotime$v1r.pseudotime
D = 0.21438, p-value < 2.2e-16
alternative hypothesis: two-sided

    Two-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test

data:  p14.v2r.pseudotime$v2r.pseudotime and p56.v2r.pseudotime$v2r.pseudotime
D = 0.10572, p-value = 1.892e-13
alternative hypothesis: two-sided
